    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="147"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-06T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 6, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 6—5:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. My telegram number 4, January 4, 9 p.m. After my third conversation there is
                    no indication that the Foreign Minister<note n="9" xml:id="d147fn9">Miguel
                        Cruchaga Tocornal.</note> has <pb facs="0331" n="243" xml:id="pg_243"/> been
                    active in advancing any proposal, that he has made any tangible progress or that
                    he has revealed to anyone what ideas he may have.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
